A man complaining of chest and back pains was found to have an acupuncture needle that had been lodged in his gut for 40 years.

Xu Long, 60, from the city of Jiujiang in south-eastern China's Jiangxi Province, had been treated with acupuncture while serving in the military in 1974 to cure stomach ache.

He said: 'The only time I ever had acupuncture was while in the army. 

'I recall I had an ongoing stomach ache at the time which hurt for two days and two nights.

